entries.title: British nationals killed 'attempting humanitarian evacuation from Soledar', family statement says
entries.description: Two British nationals were killed while attempting a "humanitarian evacuation" from the Ukrainian town of Soledar, a family statement has said.

entries.title: Hundreds of seats on Eurostar trains left unsold to avoid long queues at stations
entries.description: Hundreds of seats on Eurostar trains from London to the continent are deliberately being left unsold so long queues don't build up at stations, the company has admitted.

entries.title: 'Unprecedented danger': Doomsday Clock moves 10 seconds closer to midnight as Ukraine war rages
entries.description: The Doomsday Clock has been set at 90 seconds to midnight - representing a time of "unprecedented danger" - largely because of Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

entries.title: Blockbusters are back, first-timers rule, and a few notable snubs - the Oscar nominations talking points
entries.description: The 2023 Oscar nominations have now been revealed - and while a few were dead certs, there are some surprises too.

entries.title: Russian football teams to remain banned from European competitions
entries.description: Russian football teams are set to remain banned from European competitions as the war on Ukraine continues, Sky News understands.

entries.title: Fashion house says no animals were harmed as controversial lion head dress sparks uproar
entries.description: A fashion house says no animals were harmed in the making of a dress featuring an ultra-realistic lion's head seen on Kylie Jenner's shoulder and the catwalk at Paris fashion week.

entries.title: 'Nobody expected this': Scientists stunned by spiders who can regrow lost anuses
entries.description: Scientists say they are stunned after discovering sea spiders have the ability to grow new reproductive organs and an anus.

entries.title: 'Golden boy' mummy 'digitally unwrapped' for first time
entries.description: A mummified teenager with a heart of gold has been "digitally unwrapped" approximately 2,300 years after he was buried.

entries.title: 'Angry' and 'hostile': What we know about California shooting gunman
entries.description: The sole suspect in a Chinese New Year shooting which killed 11 people at a California dance hall has been named as Huu Can Tran.

entries.title: WHO urges 'immediate action' after 300 cough syrup child deaths
entries.description: The World Health Organisation (WHO) has called for "immediate and concerted action" after the deaths of more than 300 children were linked to contaminated cough syrup last year.

entries.title: Man whose identity was used by prolific mafia boss arrested in Sicily
entries.description: A man whose identity was used by Italy's most wanted mafia boss - Matteo Messina Denaro - has been arrested in Sicily.

entries.title: 11 confirmed dead after Chinese New Year mass shooting, as CCTV shows 'hero' confronting gunman
entries.description: CCTV has been released showing a member of the public disarming a gunman in California - just minutes after he fatally shot 11 people at a nearby Chinese New Year celebration.

entries.title: Former Hells Angels leader and 49 alleged collaborators appear in Spanish court
entries.description: A former leader of the Hells Angels in Europe could face 13 years in prison if he is convicted of running a chapter of the motorcycle club linked with organised crime on the Spanish island of Mallorca.

entries.title: Suspected mastermind in killings of British journalist and indigenous expert in the Amazon is named
entries.description: A Colombian fish trader is set to be indicted as the mastermind of last year's killing of British journalist Dom Phillips and indigenous expert Bruno Pereira.
